{
  "texts": [
    "This underscores the importance to fine-tune capable generative models to improve the RQA system's performance.",
    "We follow the procedure outlined in Appendix D and Appendix E to obtain ⟨q, a, p⟩ pairs from documentation data.",
    "For Databricks, we first use our sampling algorithm to obtain 600 passages for training, and 75 for validation and for testing.",
    "For Faire, we sampled 300 passages for training as Faire has fewer documents, and 75 for validation and for testing.",
    "We then use ChatGPT (OpenAI, 2022b) as the LLM to generate two questions for each sampled passage, and GPT-4-turbo (OpenAI, 2023) to generate an answer for each ⟨q, p⟩ pair (see Appendix B for more details)."
  ]
}